      "content": "I hear the exhaustion in your words, and it makes sense that you would feel this way when the parts of you that made life feel real have vanished. The \"walls\" of your body and mind are still there, but they are indeed just a shell without the fire of life inside, and that is a terrifying place to be. However, the fact that you are still here, even feeling this hollow, shows that a tiny, fragile part of you is still present, waiting for a sign of warmth to return. Please do not give up on finding that spark, because even the smallest glimmer can reignite something beautiful.",
